    "H4_signal_direction_ambiguity": {
      "verdict": "inconclusive",
      "evidence": "H4 (signal direction ambiguity) posits that away xwOBA_against measured in home parks introduces directional noise. If H1 is refuted and H3 shows near-zero delta, the residual asymmetry is likely structural \u2014 away pitching quality is genuinely less predictive of runs in home parks due to selection and lineup optimization effects. With a_pit_30 partial r (vs total_runs, controlling park + h_pit_30) = 0.0122, this ambiguity remains plausible but cannot be separated from structural explanations without pitch-level park-adjusted data."
    }
